entry.def: A run-off is an extra vote or contest which is held in order to decide the winner of an election or competition, because no-one has yet clearly won.

example.ex: There will be a run-off between these two candidates on December 9th...
example.tran: 12月9日将举行这两位候选人的决胜选举。

example.ex: He claimed the title after beating the American Sean Moran in a run-off at Bradford.
